.TH "BSON_READER_NEW_FROM_FD" "3" "2014-05-29" "libbson"
.SH NAME
bson_reader_new_from_fd()
.SH "SYNOPSIS"

.nf
.nf
bson_reader_t *
bson_reader_new_from_fd (int  fd,
                         bool close_on_destroy);
.fi
.fi

.SH "PARAMETERS"

.TP
.B .B fd
A valid file-descriptor.
.LP
.TP
.B .B close_on_destroy
true if
.B fd
should be
.B close()
'd when the reader is destroyed.
.LP

.SH "DESCRIPTION"

The
.BR bson_reader_new_from_fd(3)
function shall create a new
.BR bson_reader_t
that will read from the provided file-descriptor.

_fd_
.BR MUST
be in blocking mode.

If
.B close_fd
is true, then
.B fd
will be closed when the
.BR bson_reader_t
is destroyed with
.BR bson_reader_destroy(3)
\&.

.SH "RETURNS"

A newly allocated
.BR bson_reader_t
that should be freed with
.BR bson_reader_destroy
\&.


